&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Admissions Manager – Operations and Images &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic and dynamic Admissions Manager to join the Operations and Images Directorate at Great Ormond Street Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have 12 Main Surgical specialities who have a high number of admissions organised on a daily basis, which the Admissions Manager would support in managing. The role will work alongside the Assistant Service Manager, Theatres Matron and Team Leaders to ensure operational efficiency in the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have excellent data management, analytical skills and well developed networking, team working and written and verbal communication skills, have the ability to work independently and to adapt and prioritise work to ensure the continuous delivery of effective outcomes and high quality experience. Along with this we are looking for an individual with a strong knowledge of RTT and experience managing a team of administrative staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This application process may close earlier than advertised, so please do not hesitate to apply if you are interested. For any further details, please contact Claire Fletcher via email to claire.fletcher2@gosh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claire Fletcher - Assistant Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;claire.fletcher2@gosh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 4123&lt;/p&gt;
